{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Remove all VAT on applicable Licensed Taxis",
        "additional_details": "Many taxi drivers are investing in electric, wheelchair-accessible vehicles that have been reported to have already cut London taxi emissions by 59%. The 20% VAT can add thousands of pounds to costs for self-employed drivers. Buses and trains get VAT relief; we believe taxis deserve the same to help keep cities clean and mobile.",
        "background": "Remove VAT charges for all applicable licensed public-hire taxis, including London black cabs. Buses and trains are zero-rated for VAT under the VAT Act 1994. All licensed taxis, regardless of income, should receive the same treatment as public transport to support clean, accessible travel.",
